585  /// \brief Returns true if an argument of type Ty needs to be passed in a
586  /// contiguous block of registers in calling convention CallConv.
587  bool functionArgumentNeedsConsecutiveRegisters(
588  Type *Ty, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool isVarArg) const override {
589  // We support any array type as "consecutive" block in the parameter
590  // save area. The element type defines the alignment requirement and
591  // whether the argument should go in GPRs, FPRs, or VRs if available.
592  //
593  // Note that clang uses this capability both to implement the ELFv2
594  // homogeneous float/vector aggregate ABI, and to avoid having to use
595  // "byval" when passing aggregates that might fully fit in registers.
596  return Ty->isArrayTy();
597  }
